Job Purpose

As a Mechanical Design Intern, you'll be involved in all stages of the high-voltage traction system life cycle, from architecture to design and validation, right through to production. You'll be at the forefront of supporting the various production lines, whether in Quebec, China or India. You'll be at the heart of a team of experts from all fields, and you'll have to use your imagination and creativity to ensure the efficiency and quality of Dana TM4 traction systems.

Job Duties and Responsibilities

Responsibilities:

- Design mechanical parts and assemblies for traction systems (motors and inverters);

- Consider thermal and structural constraints;

- Perform analytical calculations and collaborate with the advanced calculations team;

- Assemble and validate new prototypes or proofs of concept;

- Support production start-up;

- Participate in and lead design reviews of components and complete products;

Requirements:

- Bachelor's degree in mechanical engineering or equivalent field;

- Experience in automotive mechanical design, an asset;

- Knowledge of the following manufacturing processes, an asset: metal and plastic injection molding, stamping.

- Resourcefulness

- Interest in transportation electrification an asset;

- Knowledge of NX and Team Center, an asset

- Demonstrated ability to document work;

- Ability to work in multidisciplinary teams;

INTERNSHIP - FIELD ENGINEER

Working at EBC means joining a growing construction company, on projects across Canada, in diverse and stimulating sectors. It also means working for a company that cares about the health and well-being of its employees and offers various programs and initiatives that promote wellness. At EBC, you will benefit from exciting professional development opportunities. During your internship, you will be involved or oversee duties usually assigned to a Field Engineer. You will assist the Project Manager in various tasks pertaining to the job site, including planning, organizing, and supporting project execution works; from negotiations with suppliers and subcontractors to providing support with work methods. You will also develop and suggest improvements to design standards, advise, and solve complex design and engineering issues on site.

Reach your full potential with us!

\u200B

RESPONSIBILITIES
• Monitor works daily through the technical and administrative tasks assigned to you ;
• Plan and oversee works coordination with foremen, surveyors, superintendents, engineers, project managers and subcontractors ;
• Prepare and follow up on technical issues in plans and specifications ;
• Prepare, monitor, analyze and manage subcontractor files ;
• Contribute to contract negotiations when necessary ;
• Contribute to project scheduling;
• Obtain permits and authorizations required to carry out works ;
• Plan and check material orders as needed ;
• Follow-up on "Conflict detection" when the project is executed in BIM ;
• Assist, review and communicate technical questions and change requests to the customer representative and follow-up when required;
• Plan, supervise and contribute to the development of appropriate construction methods and processes per contractual requirements, while respecting current health and -safety requirements ;
• Participate in site meetings with various project stakeholders ;
• Follow up and manage deficiencies at the end of the project ;
• Contribute to traffic management when required.

Requirements
• Bachelor's degree in Civil Engineering or Construction Engineering, in progress ;
• Relevant experience in engineering or construction is an important asset ;
• A driver's license and/or ability to travel may be required in some cases.

SKILLS AND ATTITUDES REQUIRED
• Is versatile and adaptable ;
• Is a fast learner ;
• Respects deadlines ;
• Possesses strong teamwork skills.

Benefits \u200B

An internship at EBC means:
• You actively participate in larger-than-life construction projects ;
• You work on projects across our vast Canadian territory, offering exceptional professional and personal experiences ;
• Colleagues are delighted to share time and knowledge with our interns and their infectious passion about their work ;
• The perfect opportunity to enter the workforce ;
• Advantageous compensation and generous remote project incentives ;
• The possibility to secure a position at EBC upon graduation ;
• An unforgettable experience.
